History of Magic was the dullest subject on their schedule. Pro\-fessor Binns, who taught it, was their only ghost teacher, and the most exciting thing that ever happened in his classes was his enter\-ing the room through the blackboard. Ancient and shriveled, many people said he hadn\rquote t noticed he was dead. He had simply got up to teach one day and left his body behind him in an armchair in front of the staffroom fire; his routine had not varied in the slightest since.\par
