\ldblquote Homework \emdash  compose a poem about my defeat of the Wagga Wagga Werewolf! Signed copies of \i Magical Me\i0  to the author of the best one!\rdblquote\par
The class began to leave. Harry returned to the back of the room, where Ron and Hermione were waiting.\par
\ldblquote Ready?\rdblquote  Harry muttered.\par
\ldblquote Wait till everyone\rquote s gone,\rdblquote  said Hermione nervously. \ldblquote All right \'85\rdblquote\par
She approached Lockhart\rquote s desk, a piece of paper clutched tightly in her hand, Harry and Ron right behind her.\par
\ldblquote Er \emdash  Professor Lockhart?\rdblquote  Hermione stammered. \ldblquote I wanted to \emdash  to get this book out of the library. Just for background read\-ing.\rdblquote  She held out the piece of paper, her hand shaking slightly. \ldblquote But the thing is, it\rquote s in the Restricted Section of the library, so I need a teacher to sign for it \emdash  I\rquote m sure it would help me under\-stand what you say in \i Gadding with Ghouls\i0  about slow-acting ven\-oms \emdash\rdblquote\par
