Hermione continued as though she hadn\rquote t heard him.\par
\ldblquote We don\rquote t have to worry about that yet, though, because we add those bits last. \'85\rdblquote\par
Ron turned, speechless, to Harry, who had another worry.\par
\ldblquote D\rquote you realize how much we\rquote re going to have to steal, Her\-mione? Shredded skin of a boomslang, that\rquote s definitely not in the students\rquote  cupboard. What\rquote re we going to do, break into Snape\rquote s pri\-vate stores? I don\rquote t know if this is a good idea. \'85\rdblquote\par
Hermione shut the book with a snap.\par
\ldblquote Well, if you two are going to chicken out, fine,\rdblquote  she said. There were bright pink patches on her cheeks and her eyes were brighter than usual. \ldblquote\i I\i0  don\rquote t want to break rules, you know. \i I\i0  think threat\-ening Muggle-borns is far worse than brewing up a difficult po\-tion. But if you don\rquote t want to find out if it\rquote s Malfoy, I\rquote ll go straight to Madam Pince now and hand the book back in \emdash\rdblquote\par
\ldblquote I never thought I\rquote d see the day when you\rquote d be persuading us to break rules,\rdblquote  said Ron. \ldblquote All right, we\rquote ll do it. But not toenails, okay?\rdblquote\par
\ldblquote How long will it take to make, anyway?\rdblquote  said Harry as Her\-mione, looking happier, opened the book again.\par
\ldblquote Well, since the fluxweed has got to be picked at the full moon and the lacewings have got to be stewed for twenty-one days \'85 I\rquote d say it\rquote d be ready in about a month, if we can get all the ingredients.\rdblquote\par
\ldblquote A month?\rdblquote  said Ron. \ldblquote Malfoy could have attacked half the Muggle-borns in the school by then!\rdblquote  But Hermione\rquote s eyes nar\-rowed dangerously again, and he added swiftly, \ldblquote But it\rquote s the best plan we\rquote ve got, so full steam ahead, I say.\rdblquote\par
However, while Hermione was checking that the coast was clear for them to leave the bathroom, Ron muttered to Harry, \ldblquote It\rquote ll be a lot less hassle if you can just knock Malfoy off his broom tomor\-row.\rdblquote\par
